<title>ITALY: Italy says car scheme extension costs 135 bln lire.</title>
<headline>Italy says car scheme extension costs 135 bln lire.</headline>
<dateline>ROME 1997-07-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>The extension of Italy's car incentive scheme, announced on Wednesday, will cost around 153 billion lire, but this will be more than covered by increased revenue, said Industry Minister PierLuigi Bersani.</p>
<p>&quot;We calculate that the net revenue from the scheme for the whole of 1997 from vehicles sold will be more than 800 billion lire,&quot; he told a news conference.</p>
<p>Italy introduced the scheme at the start of the year to run from January to end-September, whereby owners of cars older than 10 years could trade them in for scrapping in return for a price discount on the purchase of a new car.</p>
<p>Bersani today announced the extension of the scheme to the end of July 1998, but with lower payments.</p>
